node.text: The Fifty returns for 2021. Despite the challenges of a low snow year, a record breaking avalanche year, the lingering effects of a global pandemic and a closed border between Canada and the US, the winter of 2021 had its successes. From Montana to Alaska, Colorado to California, the third year of The Fifty bring some amazing stories, the requisite amount of suffering, some laughs and some good ole backcountry education alongside some the best mountain athletes in the world. All episodes coming out in Fall 2021.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cody Townsend on July 29, 2021 tagging @nick_russelll. May be an image of 1 person, nature and tree.

node.text: Introducing #NightmaresWithNick. It's always good to have that one friend that says 'yes' to every harebrained, dumb idea you may have. In the past couple years, that reliable buddy has been @nick_russelll. At one point of this ridiculous epic, Nick and I realized that for some reason, a lot of the ridiculous sufferfests on @the.fifty.project, Nick has been my partner, hence the #NightmaresWithNick moniker. It's a good thing to be able to laugh at when you're nine hours in on day three of this type of shit.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Cody Townsend in Plakias Beach with @elysesaugstad, and @jimthornburg. May be an image of nature.

node.text: This is possibly one of the coolest places I've ever climbed. I mean, it's not like I have a laundry list of climbing spot accolades since I barely climb but still... Anyways, I saw a photo the legendary photographer @jimthornburg posted of this spot in Crete. It looked like a space laser sliced a mountain in half. Since @elysesaugstad and I decided to vacation in the greek isles this summer, I really wanted to get to this spot exactly. Sure enough, was lucky to link up with a Cretan climbing pioneer, Vasili, and try my hands and feet up this beautiful limestone wall. It was really really friggin fun as you can tell from my stoke of leading up this Cretan Classic.

node.text:
NEW FIFTY Ep. The van walk around video is live on my YouTube channel, found at the link in my bio. This Bonus Ep. is a video tour of the build by @alpinevansllc and what goes into making this a van that is built for winter, for skiing and for life on the road. It's pretty friggin sweet if I don't say so myself.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
FYI, Alpine Vans is taking orders right now and builds start at $32k. Both of those items are a near miracle for the van building world right now.

node.text:
If there is one thing you know about @yeti , it's that their gear is friggin tough. Like tougher than a two-dollar steak tough. Their bags are no exception. From my Panga 100 that's been to the saltwater marshes of Africa to 10k feet up the side of St. Elias, to the new Crossroads line of luggage, the stuff is built to last a long damn time. It's the only sponsor I have where I get one product and specifically ask to not get replacements since the product lasts so long. 

📷: @bjarnesalen @ngkelley

node.text:
I'm proud to see @salomon taking a company wide approach to becoming a far more sustainable company. On the background, I've personally witnessed years of development of a plan to shift the companies impact in everything from carbon output to raw material use. It's not an overnight shift as transforming the way a company has been operating for decades ain't easy. But there are some massive shifts the company has been forcing itself to take to have less impact on the outdoor environments we all enjoy. Today's announcement is how we as athletes are being held accountable, take a look at video #4 in Salomon's 'Sustainability Stories'. Link in Bio.

📸: @bjarnesalen

node.text: The Fifty returns for 2021. Despite the challenges of a low snow year, a record breaking avalanche year, the lingering effects of a global pandemic and a closed border between Canada and the US, the winter of 2021 had its successes. From Montana to Alaska, Colorado to California, the third year of The Fifty bring some amazing stories, the requisite amount of suffering, some laughs and some good ole backcountry education alongside some the best mountain athletes in the world. All episodes coming out in Fall 2021.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Cody Townsend on June 28, 2021 tagging @smithoptics. May be an image of 1 person, sitting and outdoors.

node.text:
I always find it weird when people post photos like these. Posed forced laugh, obvious self-obsession, need for self-validation and some really disconnected meaningless caption like, "Smile. It's your day". Yet here I am, doing the same damn thing because my job is centered around all of those things above. Okay. That's my not-skiing summer thought of the day. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
📸: @smithoptics
